item.title: Wuhan streets described as 'eerie.' See what they look like now
item.description: The Wuhan coronavirus has left the streets of Wuhan, China, virtually empty. As the virus spreads to every part of China, CNN's David Culver speaks with an American college student in Shanghai who says finding food has gotten increasingly difficult.

item.title: Number of Iranian students turned back at US airports is growing

item.title: Larry Nassar's abuse victims offered $215M
item.description: USA Gymnastics offered Larry Nassar's victims a $215 million settlement on Thursday as part of a plan for the organization to exit bankruptcy.

item.title: Indian man killed in police shoot-out after holding 23 children hostage at fake birthday party
item.description: A man who held 23 children hostage after inviting them to a fake birthday party for his daughter has been killed by police in northern India, local authorities said Friday.

item.title: Church of England apologizes for saying only married heterosexuals should have sex
item.description: Top archbishops in the Church of England have apologized for guidance issued by the church last week that said only married heterosexuals should have sex -- while same-sex or heterosexual Christians in civil partnerships should remain abstinent.

item.title: Gwyneth Paltrow's 'Goop' treatments slammed by UK health chief

item.title: WWE stock gets body slammed after co-presidents step down

item.description: A state of emergency has been declared in Australia's capital city of Canberra as bushfires move rapidly in the area, according to authorities from the Australian Capital Territory (ACT).

item.title: Record-breaking Nike shoes to be banned
item.description: A range of high-tech Nike shoes which have revolutionized running have escaped a ban, but prototypes with thick soles and several carbon fiber plates are to be outlawed in competition in a bid to preserve the integrity of athletics.

item.title: Reward offered to remove tire stuck on 13ft crocodile's neck for years

item.title: Peppa Pig voice actress Harley Bird to step down after 13 years

item.title: Dominic Thiem sets up first Australian Open final with victory over Alexander Zverev

item.title: Dramatic video shows bushfire overtake firefighters
item.description: A timelapse shows just how quickly a bushfire in Australia overtook firefighters as they fought to contain it.

item.title: Wetlands are disappearing three times faster than forests
item.description: While musicians and movie stars campaign vocally to protect our rainforests and oceans, the world's wetlands rarely get the same level of public support. They are in many ways the planet's unglamorous, unsung heroes -- yet by one estimate wetlands are disappearing three times faster than forests.

item.title: First Italian city to offer $1 homes
Millions of Syrian children deprived of basic rights by war
item.description: A UN report focused solely on children in Syria states that five million have been displaced in the fighting, with nine years of war robbing them of their childhood and subjecting them to "unabated violations of their rights". CNN's Arwa Damon reports.
